    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "The error message should be clearer. It could say &quot;release version 17 not supported by Maven Runner&quot; or &quot;…not supported by module language level&quot; or &quot;…conflicts with maven property &#39;maven.compiler.target&#39; or something like that. Incomplete error messages are a pet peeve of mine."
  } ],
  "answers" : [ {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 36734,
      "reputation" : 405060,
      "user_id" : 104891,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/0ff652685122f4500dd4f3c21fb32da2?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "CrazyCoder",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/104891/crazycoder"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1618432028,
    "creation_date" : 1618432028,
    "answer_id" : 67098665,
    "question_id" : 67098514,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>See <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/12900859/104891\">this answer</a> for the relevant screenshots. Make sure all the source/target levels are configured correctly in all the dialogs. It may be a typo somewhere and 17 is used instead of 1.7 (Java 7).</p>\n<p>Inspect <code>.idea/misc.xml</code> file in the project directory, make sure it specifies the correct versions. See also the language levels specified in <code>*.iml</code> module files and in <code>.idea/compiler.xml</code> file.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 8529,
      "reputation" : 35952,
      "user_id" : 15441,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 92,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/4a1893b18ee404523fb4bf12479de892?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "hawkeye",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15441/hawkeye"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1618748814,
    "creation_date" : 1618748814,
    "answer_id" : 67148514,
    "question_id" : 67098514,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I had this issue when I was using the default Ant run. When I switched the project to maven with the maven-compiler-plugin with java version set this issue went away.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 21421052,
      "reputation" : 51,
      "user_id" : 15779318,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/45741ab0e7d06376051e8601d63f8fa4?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Boulder_on",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15779318/boulder-on"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1619554134,
    "creation_date" : 1619554134,
    "answer_id" : 67290008,
    "question_id" : 67098514,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>In order to fix this I had to change the Ant build setting Execution -&gt; Jun under JDK. For some reason the default was JDK 11, everywhere else I has specified JDK 16. Once I set this to JDK 16 the problem went away.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 15963683,
      "reputation" : 21,
      "user_id" : 11519987,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/EF4Qc.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Viacheslav Zholnovach",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/11519987/viacheslav-zholnovach"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 2,
    "last_activity_date" : 1621841830,
    "creation_date" : 1621841830,
    "answer_id" : 67668265,
    "question_id" : 67098514,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>In my case, updating <code>.idea/misc.xml</code> didn't help.\nI was upgrading from Intellij 2020.2 -&gt; Intellij 2020.4 -&gt; Intellij 2020.1.1.\nEnded up with a reset: <code>File -&gt; Manage IDE Settings -&gt; Restore Default Settings...</code></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 21558810,
      "reputation" : 129,
      "user_id" : 15893640,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1cf5d70b5aaa18b5079600d85a8d170a?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "edine-noella",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15893640/edine-noella"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 10,
    "last_activity_date" : 1622794210,
    "creation_date" : 1622794210,
    "answer_id" : 67833709,
    "question_id" : 67098514,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I have faced the same error while trying to use version 16.This is because the new version you are trying to use is unstable.</p>\n<ol>\n<li><p>you have to uninstall the version 17  go to:  <strong>file</strong> -&gt; <strong>project\nstructure</strong> -&gt; <strong>SDKs</strong> .delete sdk 17 by right clicking on it and\nthen delete.\n<a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/PE9oQ.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\">right click on highlighted version(in your case its 17)</a></p>\n</li>\n<li><p>now you have to change project sdk go to: <strong>file</strong> -&gt; <strong>project\nstructure</strong> -&gt; <strong>project</strong> . select the previous version which use\nto work for you , in my case its <strong>15 java version &quot;15.0.2&quot;</strong>.  set\nproject language level to default (<strong>SDK default(15-Text blocks)</strong>)</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/I5DCY.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\">changing project sdk and project language level</a></p>\n</li>\n<li><p>the last part is to change the project configuration sdk go to your\nnavigation bar where you debug your project then select <strong>edit\nconfigurations</strong> . select the sdk 16 for your project (in my case\nits 15)\n<a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/WwiIo.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\">to change the project configuration sdk</a></p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n"
  }, {
