      "account_id" : 25365627,
      "reputation" : 1,
      "user_id" : 19180247,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjqTUJ4ZirW2BsGGm2dhHQ6e25ZdkL8MzJ_b8x9-w=k-s256",
      "display_name" : "Manjunatha D",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/19180247/manjunatha-d"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1713417379,
    "creation_date" : 1713417379,
    "answer_id" : 78345008,
    "question_id" : 67098514,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>check below three properties in the pom.xml\nVersions should match to the available java SDK version.</p>\n<pre><code> &lt;maven.compiler.source&gt;17&lt;/maven.compiler.source&gt;\n &lt;maven.compiler.target&gt;17&lt;/maven.compiler.target&gt;\n &lt;java.version&gt;17&lt;/java.version&gt;\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 4674010,
      "reputation" : 1109,
      "user_id" : 3785010,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/64cfa0011df0ade68f90c2466bef8004?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "IntelligenceGuidedByExperience",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3785010/intelligenceguidedbyexperience"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1722221580,
    "creation_date" : 1722221580,
    "answer_id" : 78805258,
    "question_id" : 67098514,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>2024-07-29: The real problem in using IntelliJ, even the newest one, 2024.1.1 Ultimate Edition, is there are too many places where a Java version has to be specified.  If any of them are wrong or inconsistent, any number of errors can occurs.</p>\n<p>Bottom line: JetBrains needs to change IntelliJ to have &quot;one version of the truth&quot; (one single place) where you specify which version of Java you want to use.  Until that happens, posts like the ones in this thread will continue to cause the confusion and hair-pulling among developers trying to tell IntelliJ what version of Java is desired for a given project.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 11253033,
      "reputation" : 20843,
      "user_id" : 8253662,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/FuMpZ.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Mahesh Jamdade",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/8253662/mahesh-jamdade"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1724278001,
    "last_edit_date" : 1724278001,
    "creation_date" : 1724277525,
    "answer_id" : 78899127,
    "question_id" : 67098514,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<h3>Running Spring application from terminal</h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Note that this is not necessary if your are using IntelliJ, Only if you are running the spring boot application from terminal otherwise skip to step 2</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Firstly check what version of Java is your system using by running <code>java --version</code> In my case my system had java 16 path configured</p>\n<pre><code>mahesh@Maheshs-MacBook-Air-M1-3 expenses-backend % java --version\nopenjdk 16.0.1 2021-04-20\nOpenJDK Runtime Environment (build 16.0.1+9-24)\nOpenJDK 64-Bit Server VM (build 16.0.1+9-24, mixed mode, sharing)\nmahesh@Maheshs-MacBook-Air-M1-3 expenses-backend % \n</code></pre>\n<p>You can also check the exact path by running <code>echo $JAVA_HOME</code></p>\n<p>Using Step 2 download or select the JDK of your choice, Once you follow the below steps to setup your JDK of your choice update the <code>JAVA_HOME</code> path in <code>~/.zshrc</code> or <code>~/.bashrc</code> based on the shell you are using bash or zsh</p>\n<p>and finally update the <code>java.version</code> in pom.xml</p>\n<h3>If you are using IntelliJ</h3>\n<p>Now, Check in your pom.xml What version of java does your project need my project has version 17 specified while in <code>pom.xml</code>, So I changed that to 20</p>\n<pre><code>&lt;java.version&gt;20&lt;/java.version&gt;\n</code></pre>\n<p>Then in your Intellij IDE go to <code>File -&gt; Project structure -&gt; SDKs</code>\nYou should see the list of Sdks on the left, if you don't see them click on the + icon to add a new JDK</p>\n<p>Intellij should help you detect available JDKs in your environment, if your system already has the JDK that your are looking for (e.g JDK 20 in this case) then choose it.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/V00DKIbt.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/V00DKIbt.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n<p>If not you can download the required JDK from the vendor of your choice</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/jK4caHFd.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/jK4caHFd.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n<p>Finally after you apply and save click on <code>File -&gt; Reload from disk</code> to reindex the selected JDK</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3569155,
      "reputation" : 3710,
      "user_id" : 2979955,
